  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="394a-d994-3808-bb19" name="Flame-thrower" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="4" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry, Gun, and Unarmoured Tank Teams re-roll successful Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower and the Unit is automatically Pinned Down. Armoured Tank Teams use their Top armour for Armour Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower.

Flame-throwers may shoot in Defensive Fire. However, while a Unit that is Hit by a Flame-thrower is Pinned Down, this does not automatically stop the assault. The defender still needs to score five (or eight) hits as normal to stop the assault as normal.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="aa86-a5db-aa6d-9cce" name="Crafty" publicationId="4021-7322-ad7d-e1d9" page="4" hidden="false">
      <comment>added by AncestralHeritage</comment>
      <description>Crafty Tanks have better Tactics ratings.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ecac-4224-405c-3e59" name="Flammable" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="4" hidden="false">
      <description>Flammable Tanks have worse Motivation and Assault ratings.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3808-f29e-c461-34b7" name="Heavy Tank" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="4" hidden="false">
      <description>Heavy Tanks have a better Counterattack rating.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="19b9-fe56-ba9b-2244" name="Not One Step back" publicationId="4021-7322-ad7d-e1d9" page="4" hidden="false">
      <comment>added by AncestralHeritage</comment>
      <description>Units with Not One Step Backhave a better Last Stand rating.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d302-3fb2-099e-b54b" name="For the Motherland" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry with For the Motherland have a better Assault rating.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cd04-8d13-53bf-4376" name="Komissar" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>While their Komissar team is In Command, a Unit has a better Motivation, as shown in the Komissar column.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="69e8-6dda-6615-4f9e" name="Redemption" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Penal Company is placed on the table during Deployment (but not if it is placed outside the normal Deployment Area using the Spearhand rule), the player may immediatley Move its Teams at Tactical or Dash speed.

This movement may not use any Movement Orders, and may not take a Team within:
- 16&quot;/40cm of an enemy Team it is not Concealed from,
- 8&quot;/20cm of any enemy Team,
- 16&quot;/40cm of the enemy Deployment Area or any Objective outside your own Deployment Area.

A Penal Company may not be placed in Reserve.
A Penal Company never benefits from Bulletproof Cover.
A Penal COmpany can prevent the enemy from Holding an Objective, but cannot Hold an Objective. Ignore a Destroyed Penal Company when calculating Victory Points.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0bf9-04ce-c0b9-6b01" name="Unit Transport" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>The Unit Leader of the Transport Attachment must end the Movement Step within 6&quot;/15cm of the Unit Leader of its Passenger Unit while on the Table. If it cannot do this, then the Transport Attachment must be Sent to the Rear (see page 45 of the rulebook).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9f1a-99ae-6d34-04be" name="Urrah" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Units with Urrah may move 6&quot;/15cm (instead of 4&quot;/10cm) when Charging into Contact.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="60a6-26f9-5553-7d92" name="Sapper Body Armour" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>A Team with Sapper Body Armour rolls a die when hit in Assault combat. On a roll of 6 they are unharmed, on any other roll they are destroyed as usual.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e992-328f-63d1-0dfc" name="Pioneers" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Pioneer Teams cross Minefields safely on a roll of 2+. If they remain in the Minefield and are not Pinned Down, they may clear the Minefield automatically in their next turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e362-99dc-e7fb-253f" name="Limited 2" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Each time this Unit shoots, # number of its Teams may shoot as that Weapon rather than its usual weapons.

Each time this Unit rolls to Hit in an Assault, # number of its Teams may attack with that Weapon rather than its usual weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="79c4-5af6-d384-b219" name="Salvo" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Weapons with a ROF of &quot;salvo&quot; are Artillery weapons and fire Artillery Bombardments, but use a 10”/25cm square Salvo Template rather than the normal 6”/15cm Artillery Template.

A Salvo Template may not be placed within 6&quot;/15cm of a friendly Team.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4568-ee66-1e3c-332f" name="Flying Tank" publicationId="9f90-b6ea-6e0c-9aa3" page="5" hidden="false">
      <description>Flying Tanks have a worse Is Hit On rating, but a better Save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="fd73-4578-8d07-e9ab" name="Limited 1" publicationId="4021-7322-ad7d-e1d9" page="5" hidden="false">
      <comment>added by AncestralHeritage</comment>
      <description>Each time this Unit shoots, # number of its Teams may shoot as that Weapon rather than its usual weapons.

Each time this Unit rolls to Hit in an Assault, # number of its Teams may attack with that Weapon rather than its usual weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="bbdc-4c91-df1a-89f2" name="Bedspring Armour" publicationId="4021-7322-ad7d-e1d9" page="4" hidden="false">
      <comment>added by AncestralHeritage</comment>
      <description>If a tank protected by Bedspring Armour fails an Armour Save against a weapon with a Firepower of 5+ or 6 hitting its Side armour, roll a die.

On a roll of 5+ the Bedspring Armour protects the tank and the hit is ignored.
Otherwise the hit affects the Side armour as normal.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
